The paper deals with exploring different types of filter banks for speech recognition using end-to-end convolutional neural networks. This falls under the sub-category of Speech and Signal Processing (cs.SD) as well as Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) since speech recognition is a subfield of NLP. The paper also discusses the use of Gabor filters and Gammatone filters, which are commonly used in image processing and signal processing, respectively, indicating a possible connection to Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions rearranging the order of operations in computing filter bank features, which could potentially fall under Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) as it involves optimizing the feature extraction process.
